# What You Learned Today

## `Form`

A `Form` groups related input fields together.

Instead of validating each field separately, you can validate the entire form.

---

## `GlobalKey<FormState>`

```dart
final _formKey = GlobalKey<FormState>();
```

This gives us access to the form so we can call:

```dart
_formKey.currentState!.validate();
```

---

## `TextEditingController`

Each input field has a controller.

Example:

```dart
emailController.text
```

This retrieves the text the user entered.

Later, we'll send these values to the backend.

---

## `SnackBar`

Instead of printing to the console, we show feedback to the user.

Example:

```
Registration Successful
```

or

```
Passwords do not match
```

